    "**In class Parts I and II**\n",
    "\n",
    "(1) Create a base class call Seq. Seq should have a constructor in initialize and instance of Seq with sequence, gene name and species.\n",
    "\n",
    "(2) Create 2 methods for Seq.\n",
    "1. print_record returns the sequence\n",
    "2. overload the str function to return species, gene name : sequence\n",
    "\n",
    "(1) Create a class DNA that inherits Seq. In the constructor, use the super()\n",
    " function to make the contructor. Add a variable gene_id and\n",
    " add **kwargs also in the constructor\n",
    " \n",
    "(2) Add a method called analysis that returns then number of Gs and Cs"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "bae45be8-3e16-4148-b23a-d8cc42ccb914",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "##Part I\n",
    "\n",
    "class Seq:\n",
    "  def __init__(self,sequence,gene,species,**kwargs):\n",
    "    self.sequence=sequence\n",
    "    self.gene=gene\n",
    "    self.species=species\n",
    "  \n",
    "  def __str__(self):\n",
    "    return f\"{self.species}, {self.gene} : {self.sequence}\"\n",
    "\n",
    "  def print_record(self):\n",
    "    return self.sequence\n",
    "\n",
    "#Part II\n",
    "\n",
    "class DNA(Seq):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, sequence, gene, species, gene_id, **kwargs):\n",
    "        super().__init__(sequence, gene, species, **kwargs)\n",
    "        self.gene_id = gene_id\n",
    "\n",
    "    def analysis(self):\n",
    "        return sum(1 for x in self.sequence if x in ['G', 'C']) #adds 1 every time theres G or C and returns the total"
   ]
  },
